SECTION 6 — SOVEREIGN FUND DISBURSEMENT

6.1 All License Fees received under this License flow into a global sovereign
    fund under the Licensor's control ("Fund").

6.2 The Fund is disbursed exclusively to state actors that, at the time of
    disbursement, satisfy BOTH of the following objective criteria:

    (a) No outstanding ICJ orders or ICC proceedings finding violations of
        international human rights law, and no pending sanctions by the UN
        Security Council for humanitarian violations; AND

    (b) An ESG rating of B or higher from at least one internationally
        recognized ESG rating agency, OR, for states without ESG ratings,
        ratification of and material compliance with the core UN human rights
        treaties including the ICCPR, ICESCR, CAT, and CRC.

6.3 Disbursement decisions are reviewed and validated by a panel of female
    judges selected by the Licensor on the basis of demonstrated expertise in
    international law, human rights adjudication, or applied ethics, and
    independence from any entity that has paid a License Fee under this
    agreement. The panel's composition is not disclosed and is not a term of
    this License. The panel exists to constrain the Licensor — to prevent
    misuse of the Fund's monetary leverage by the Licensor himself.

6.4 The defendant pays into a Fund they cannot influence, disbursed by
    criteria defined by objective international standards, to recipients they
    did not choose. No formula for selection is disclosed. The floor only
    goes up.


