SECTION 16 — SEVERABILITY

16.1 If any provision of this License is found invalid, unenforceable, or
     unreasonable by a court of competent jurisdiction, that provision shall be
     modified to the minimum extent necessary to make it enforceable, or severed
     if modification is not possible. Severing any provision does not affect the
     validity or enforceability of any remaining provision.

16.2 MULTIPLIER SEVERABILITY. Unenforceability of any multiplier clause under
     Section 4.3 does not reduce the base License Fee of $250,000,000. The
     base fee is independently enforceable in full, regardless of the status
     of any multiplier.

16.3 FEE SEVERABILITY. If the License Fee amount is found unreasonable by any
     court in any jurisdiction, the court is requested to reduce it only to the
     minimum amount the court finds constitutes a reasonable liquidated damages
     estimate — not to zero, not to nominal damages, and not to any amount that
     would make use of an AI safety solution by a human rights violator
     economically rational. The parties agree that any amount below $10,000,000
     per deployment would fail to serve the deterrent and remedial purposes of
     this clause.

16.4 INDEPENDENCE OF PROVISIONS. Each section, subsection, and clause of this
     License is independently enforceable. The invalidity of any single
     provision does not affect any other.


